    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Hazel Hart Whittaker was the second wife of Republican Senator Arthur H. Vandenberg  of Michigan of Michigan. She was a 1906 graduate of the University of Michigan, where she first met Vandenberg. Whitaker worked as a newspaper reporter, including a spell as  a woman's page writer for the <title render="italic">Chicago Tribune</title>.  She married Vandenberg  in 1918 and together they raised three children, Arthur jr., Barbara, and Elizabeth, from his previous marriage.  Hazel Vandenberg died  June 10, 1950</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>
The papers,1928-1950, of Hazel Vandenberg, wife of Michigan Republican Senator, Arthur H. Vandenberg; include diaries with descriptions of social activities and daily political life in Washington; included as part of diaries are newspaper clippings, photographs, programs, and other personal miscellanea; also scrapbooks,1928-1950. </p>
    </scopecontent>
